  "prompt": "How much time does Wipro takes to send a DOJ after the background verification is done?",
  "response": "The time it takes for Wipro to send a Date of Joining (DOJ) after the completion of the background verification process can vary based on several factors, including the role, location, and specific circumstances of the hiring process. Generally, companies like Wipro strive to move candidates through the hiring process efficiently, but it might take anywhere from a few days to a few weeks for the DOJ to be communicated.\n\nIf you have been waiting for an extended period, it is advisable to reach out to your recruitment contact at Wipro for an update on your application status. They can provide you with more specific information regarding your situation.",
